Mediastinal contours are unchanged. There is mild to moderate moderate pulmonary edema, with more focal opacity seen in the right lung base, new from the prior study. Small bilateral pleural effusions are noted. There is no pneumothorax. No acute osseous abnormalities are visualized. Clips are seen within the upper abdomen.
Impression: Mild to moderate pulmonary edema, similar compared to the prior study, with more focal opacity in the right lung base concerning for an area of infection.
